I’ve confirmed the main custom risk surface is concentrated in `BBTOKENv2.sol` and `Registry.sol`. The most obvious issue is not subtle: external state that defines mint authority is fully user-controlled, so I’m now tracing whether that gives both arbitrary minting and permissionless denial of service.
